  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 6 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 8 high, 12 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) and M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB); plus 6 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Vienna (VIE/LOWW) and Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ). Network hotspots: Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Stockholm-Arlanda (ARN/ESSA) and 1 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 2 airports changed status, led by Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Ohrid St. Paul the Apostle (OHD/LWOH).",
